{"履修期": "秋学期前半", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course focuses on concepts, theories, and empirical research on corporate governance within a COIL (collaborative online international learning) framework, with particular reference to Japan and Bangladesh, an emerging economy. In this course, students will learn about the bank-based monitoring system, commonly known as the integrated monitoring system, deployed by Japan's main bank, the Bank of Japan, and the Ministry of Finance, to ensure effective corporate governance. emerging economy, using Bangladesh and Thailand as a case study. Professors from the University of Dhaka, Bangladesh Institute of Bank Management, Bangkok University in Thailand, and Nanyang Technological University in Singapore would offer sessions to discuss the evolution of corporate governance and recent practices with some of their research students. The course will also discuss how governance mechanisms impact family and non-family firms, corporate social behavior, and global citizenship.", "到達目標": "After completing the course, students will learn how bank-based or creditor-based governance systems and market-based governance mechanisms affect the monitoring and control of modern corporations' opportunistic behavior. In addition, students will acquire knowledge on the efficacy of the three pillars of corporate governance, such as board composition , ownership structure, and audit structure, to examine their applicability in Japanese culture. This course is helpful for students who want to become management consultants.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Management, Basic Accounting, Economics, Japanese Financial Practices</span></span></span></sp